## Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "Raw Data Sources (~12 GB)"
        A1[IMDb title.basics.tsv<br>12.3M titles]
        A2[IMDb title.ratings.tsv<br>1.6M rated]
        A3[TMDB v11<br>1.4M movies]
        A4[GroupLens ML-32M<br>32M ratings]
        A5[Wikipedia Plots<br>34.9K plots]
        A6[Rotten Tomatoes<br>143K movies + 1M reviews]
        A7[Indian Movies<br>50.6K films]
    end

    subgraph "Processing Pipeline"
        B1[Layer 1: Filter movies<br>Cross-reference IDs]
        B2[Layer 2: TMDB inner join]
        B3[Layer 3: Title+Year matching]
        B4[Layer 4: Title+Year → slug → reviews]
        B5[Layer 5: Chunked aggregation]
        B6[Layer 6: Direct tconst mapping]
    end

    subgraph "Output Layers (Parquet)"
        C1[movie_entity.parquet<br>730K movies, 21.5 MB]
        C2[metadata_layer.parquet<br>347K movies, 87.8 MB]
        C3[plot_layer.parquet<br>29.7K plots, 39.6 MB]
        C4[review_layer.parquet<br>927K reviews, 80.5 MB]
        C5[recommendation_layer.parquet<br>87.6K movies, 4.5 MB]
        C6[regional_layer.parquet<br>50.6K films, 1.3 MB]
    end

    A1 & A2 --> B1 --> C1
    A3 --> B2 --> C2
    A5 --> B3 --> C3
    A6 --> B4 --> C4
    A4 --> B5 --> C5
    A7 --> B6 --> C6

    C1 -.->|imdb_id PK| C2 & C3 & C4 & C5 & C6
```

